The input integer `n` represents the total number of cities.
The input integer `src` represents the source city.
The input integer `dst` represents the destination city.
The input integer `k` represents the maximum number of stops allowed.
The input 2D array `flights` represents the flights between cities, where each row represents a flight and the first element is the source city, the second element is the destination city, and the third element is the price of the flight.
